Name: BBQ Chicken Calzones
Description: If you like BBQ Chicken Pizza, you'll like this easy-to-make calzone version!
Author: TUMMY13

Name: Ground Beef and Chopped Cabbage
Description: This mixture of ground beef, cabbage, and tomatoes is given a flavor boost with the addition of red pepper flakes, garlic, and Italian seasoning.
Author: slygusa

Name: Greek Lemon Chicken and Potato Bake
Description: One-pan Greek chicken, roasted with potatoes and green beans, requires minimal attention while it cooks.
Author: Chef V

Name: Gerry's Easy Irish Stew
Description: This Irish stew of beef, potatoes, carrot, celery, and onion is easy to make as a hearty, one-pot Sunday meal. Tastes great the next day too!
Author: cricrinapoli

Name: Parmesan Crusted Tilapia Fillets
Description: This version of Parmesan-crusted tilapia uses only a few ingredients for a quick and easy dinner entree.
Author: LilSnoo

Name: Blueberry Cream Slushy
Description: My husband and I went crazy over a blueberry smoothie at a local cafe. This was our attempt to recreate it...but we actually like it better than the original!
Author: GOLDILOCKSMAIL

Name: Fennel Coleslaw
Description: Triple sec liqueur adds a hint of sweet orange flavor to a colorful slaw made of red and green cabbage tossed with thinly sliced fennel and topped with a sprinkle of pine nuts.
Author: Clarissa

Name: Fruity Curry Chicken Salad
Description: A healthy and tasty chicken salad with a fruity twist - great on a croissant or in a honey pita. Note: This salad is best if eaten the day after preparation. This allows the ingredients time to mingle, giving a fuller flavor. If desired, use nonfat mayonnaise.
Author: Karen L. Baker

Name: Roasted Pecan Banana Bread Loaves
Description: Mini banana bread loaves make it easy to eat some and freeze some for later. They have the crunch of freshly-toasted pecans and a hint of coconut flavor to boost the banana taste.
Author: atlantasassybelle

Name: Indoor Chicken Burgers on Biscuits
Description: Homemade chicken burgers are sandwiched between homemade biscuits and sauteed onions in this delicious alternative to grilled burgers.
Author: mommymeggy

Name: Easter Carrot Cheese Log
Description: A cream cheese-based dip is formed into a carrot shape and topped with Cheddar cheese is a fun Easter appetizer to serve with crackers.
Author: Montillo Italian Foods

Name: Blue Cheese and Sour Cream Potato Salad
Description: Potatoes, hard-boiled eggs, and green onions are dressed with blue cheese and sour cream in this easy potato salad perfect for a picnic.
Author: Judy

Name: Peanut Butter Pound Cake
Description: This sweet and rich pound cake has a nutty taste thanks to the addition of peanut butter and a crunchy topping of finely chopped peanuts.
Author: KOHKI730

Name: Ultimate Butter Pound Cake
Description: This is a rich and dense vanilla pound cake your family will request often. The ingredients are simple and basic, and making it is a snap.
Author: LisaK

Name: Cold Chicken Pasta Salad
Description: This vermicelli pasta salad, best served cold, is made with chicken, artichokes, and cherry tomatoes tossed in a simple lemony dressing.
Author: Say-Rah

Name: Zesty Cold Chicken Pasta Salad
Description: This quick and easy pasta salad with canned chicken, cherry tomatoes, and a zesty lemon pepper dressing makes for a tasty cold lunch.
Author: Krysie

Name: Pasta Inverno (Winter Vegetable Pasta)
Description: This whole grain pasta dish features vegetables like winter squash, green beans, and tomatoes and a sweet and sour sauce known as agrodolce.
Author: Karen Barris Calabro

Name: Quick and Easy Strawberry Cream Cheese Frosting
Description: Strawberry cream cheese frosting is quick and easy to make using strawberry flavored Jell-O(R), cream cheese, and milk; everyone loves it!
Author: kikhola13

Name: Chicken Agrodolce
Description: Chicken simmered with balsamic vinegar and orange and lemon juice are key components in this Italian sweet-sour recipe: chicken agrodolce.
Author: Divinity

Name: French Toast Variation of Eggs in a Basket
Description: This variation on eggs in a basket involves making French toast with the bread too, resulting in a quick, easy breakfast with extra protein.
Author: tverne1

Name: Aunt Judi's Easter Pineapple Raisin Sauce
Description: Pineapple raisin sauce with brown sugar is a quick and easy addition to baked ham and a crowd-pleasing part of Easter brunch or dinner.
Author: raesive

Name: Plant-Based Stuffed Green Pepper
Description: Green bell peppers stuffed with brown rice and simmered in a veggie tomato sauce are a tasty, plant-based meal that is easy to make.
Author: newday2d

Name: Vegan Cinnamon Waffles
Description: Vegan cinnamon waffles made with coconut oil and apple cider vinegar are quick and easy to prepare and a delicious start to the day.
Author: siege36

Name: Chicken Burgers with Blue Cheese
Description: These savory ground chicken burgers with crumbled blue cheese and a mayonnaise-Dijon sauce are a great choice for an easy weeknight meal.
Author: Nick Gibietis

Name: Spicy Chicken Burgers
Description: These grilled chicken burgers topped with smashed avocado and homemade coleslaw are sure to be a dinner hit for fans of spicy food.
Author: Nikip4

Name: Fresh Strawberry Shortcake Cupcakes
Description: These cute cupcakes with a fresh strawberry cream cheese filling and a swirl of whipped cream are like strawberry shortcakes in cupcake form.
Author: bunbun

Name: Cream of Wheat (Semolina) Porridge
Description: Enjoy a hot breakfast of lightly sweetened semolina porridge with this 6-ingredient cream of wheat recipe that's quick and easy to make.
Author: Oleechka

Name: Wheat Flour Halva
Description: This recipe for halva, a Persian spin on the Middle Eastern dessert, has a wheat flour base flavored with saffron, rose water, and cardamom.
Author: Soheila

Name: Baked Halva
Description: This semolina halva is doused in a clove and cinnamon syrup right after it's baked to yield a rich and sweet Greek-inspired dessert.
Author: Sophie
